question: {name1} and {name2} are sisters from {city} who love collecting signatures from {celebrity_type}. During their {vacation_type} from school, the sisters spend every afternoon collecting signatures. After {n1} weeks, {name1} and {name2} compare their autograph books, counting up the number of signatures each sister has collected. {name1} has {s1} signatures in her book, and {name2} has {s2}. The sisters have {n2} more weeks of {vacation_type}, and they decide they want to reach {goal} signatures between them by the end of the break. However, during the remaining {n2} weeks, {name1} is only able to collect signatures on weekends, reducing her weekly collection by 5 per week, while {name2} decides to increase her weekly collection. How many signatures will {name2} need to collect per week to make sure they reach their goal?
